HMD Global has launched its latest smartphone, the Nokia 2.2, which is an affordable smartphone with a dedicated Google Assistant button. The Nokia 2.2 features a quad-core MediaTek A22 chipset and a 5.71-inch HD+ display. Other impressive features for a device in this price range include face unlock, a 13MP camera with AI-assisted low-light photography, and access to Google Lens. It runs Android 9 Pie and will include “no clutter or third-party software,” said Nokia. The Nokia 2.2 is priced at €99, and is set to launch in Europe and India. HMD Global did not state whether the device would launch in other markets. 